cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of registering and synthesizing MRI and histological sections, which is a common problem in computer vision and medical imaging. The use of probabilistic models and Bayesian inference suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of landmarks and the focus on accuracy and robustness suggest that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of flexible deformation models and the focus on optimization suggest that the paper may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
